WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Tired of searching for subtitles?
Ray generates them instantly: getray.app

2
00:05:11.069 --> 00:05:13.936
You will need this.

3
00:05:25.817 --> 00:05:27.079
What does it say?

4
00:05:28.186 --> 00:05:33.647
" I belong to the warrior in whom
the old ways have joined the new."

5
00:06:37.689 --> 00:06:40.157
Good God.

6
00:06:43.728 --> 00:06:47.789
Sir. the lmperial Army of Japan
demands your surrender.

7
00:06:48.232 --> 00:06:50.826
If you lay down your arms.
you will not be harmed.

8
00:06:51.169 --> 00:06:55.697
This is not possible.
as Mr. Omura knows.

9
00:06:59.877 --> 00:07:01.811
Captain Algren.

10
00:07:01.980 --> 00:07:03.880
We will show you no quarter.

11
00:07:04.048 --> 00:07:06.710
You ride against us.
and you are the same as them.

12
00:07:07.719 --> 00:07:09.744
I'll look for you on the field.

13
00:07:30.541 --> 00:07:32.008
Captain Algren.

14
00:07:32.176 --> 00:07:34.770
Mr. Graham.

15
00:07:38.082 --> 00:07:41.449
Perhaps you can use these
for your book.

16
00:07:41.619 --> 00:07:44.053
Yes. I will. Captain.

17
00:07:47.225 --> 00:07:48.954
Godspeed.

18
00:07:50.595 --> 00:07:52.961
Mr. Graham.

19
00:09:15.847 --> 00:09:18.645
Commence firing!

20
00:10:34.525 --> 00:10:37.085
-They're covering their retreat.
-You see?

21
00:10:37.261 --> 00:10:41.027
Even the mighty Samurai
cannot stand up to the howitzers.

22
00:10:41.199 --> 00:10:44.396
-Signal the attack.
-I advise sending in skirmishers first.

23
00:10:44.569 --> 00:10:46.560
Nonsense! Full attack!

24
00:11:42.293 --> 00:11:44.523
They're coming.

25
00:12:16.894 --> 00:12:18.794
Wait for the volley.

26
00:12:30.574 --> 00:12:32.405
Second volley.

27
00:13:27.198 --> 00:13:29.462
-What on earth?
-What is happening?

28
00:14:14.278 --> 00:14:17.611
-The attack has been stopped.
-Send in the rest of the regiment.

29
00:14:22.586 --> 00:14:24.850
What happened to the warriors
at Thermopylae?

30
00:14:25.256 --> 00:14:28.020
Dead to the last man.

31
00:15:31.088 --> 00:15:32.851
Algren-san!

32
00:18:21.358 --> 00:18:24.191
Son of a bitch thinks he can win.

33
00:19:28.425 --> 00:19:32.327
They'll bring two more regiments
up here soon.

34
00:19:32.496 --> 00:19:34.555
We won't be able to stop them again.

35
00:19:35.566 --> 00:19:37.625
You do not have to die here.

36
00:19:40.671 --> 00:19:43.435
I should have died
so many times before.

37
00:19:43.974 --> 00:19:45.407
Now. you live again.

38
00:19:48.645 --> 00:19:50.840
Yes.

39
00:19:53.016 --> 00:19:55.985
It was not your time.

40
00:19:59.356 --> 00:20:01.654
It's not over.

41
00:20:47.971 --> 00:20:49.370
What is this?

42
00:20:53.644 --> 00:20:57.978
-This is madness. He's going to attack?
-Yes.

43
00:21:06.256 --> 00:21:09.316
He's defeated!
He must accept his shame!

44
00:21:21.305 --> 00:21:23.705
Kill him. All of them.

45
00:21:23.874 --> 00:21:26.274
Now!

46
00:21:30.347 --> 00:21:31.678
My horse!

47
00:22:24.601 --> 00:22:25.863
Fire!

48
00:23:02.906 --> 00:23:04.237
Ready!

49
00:23:07.611 --> 00:23:08.873
Aim!

50
00:23:14.217 --> 00:23:15.582
Fire!

51
00:23:21.725 --> 00:23:23.215
Fire at will!

52
00:24:22.319 --> 00:24:23.616
Backward!

53
00:26:33.617 --> 00:26:35.050
No.

54
00:26:42.159 --> 00:26:44.889
You have your honor again.

55
00:26:47.097 --> 00:26:49.361
Let me die with mine.

56
00:26:58.775 --> 00:27:00.800
Help me up.

57
00:27:20.397 --> 00:27:22.092
Are you ready?

58
00:27:29.239 --> 00:27:32.902
I will miss our conversations.

59
00:28:19.456 --> 00:28:21.788
Perfect.

60
00:28:28.398 --> 00:28:31.595
They are all...

61
00:28:32.602 --> 00:28:34.729
...perfect.

62
00:30:02.826 --> 00:30:06.455
On behalf of the United States of America...

63
00:30:07.397 --> 00:30:12.630
...the signing of this treaty will usher in
an era of unprecedented prosperity...

64
00:30:12.802 --> 00:30:16.932
...and cooperation between
our two great nations.

65
00:30:17.273 --> 00:30:19.002
On behalf of the Emperor...

66
00:30:19.175 --> 00:30:22.941
...we are pleased to have
successfully concluded this...

67
00:30:26.316 --> 00:30:28.614
...negotiation.

68
00:32:12.822 --> 00:32:15.655
This is Katsumoto's sword.

69
00:32:16.993 --> 00:32:19.689
He would have wanted you to have it...

70
00:32:20.864 --> 00:32:23.924
...that the strength of the Samurai
be with you always.

71
00:32:30.006 --> 00:32:31.564
He hoped...

72
00:32:32.208 --> 00:32:34.403
...with his last breath...

73
00:32:34.811 --> 00:32:38.178
...that you would remember the ancestors
who held this sword...

74
00:32:39.949 --> 00:32:42.247
...and what they died for.

75
00:33:02.472 --> 00:33:04.702
You were with him...

76
00:33:05.875 --> 00:33:07.934
...at the end?

77
00:33:13.316 --> 00:33:16.774
Emperor. this man fought against you!

78
00:33:20.990 --> 00:33:22.617
Your Highness...

79
00:33:23.893 --> 00:33:28.455
...if you believe me to be your enemy.
command me...

80
00:33:28.631 --> 00:33:30.929
...and I will gladly take my life.

81
00:33:45.081 --> 00:33:49.142
I have dreamed of a unified Japan...

82
00:33:49.319 --> 00:33:55.121
...of a country strong
and independent and modern.

83
00:33:55.291 --> 00:34:01.093
And now we have railroads
and cannon. Western clothing.

84
00:34:03.032 --> 00:34:04.659
But...

85
00:34:08.037 --> 00:34:12.098
...we cannot forget who we are...

86
00:34:13.543 --> 00:34:18.037
...or where we come from.

87
00:34:30.460 --> 00:34:33.020
Ambassador Swanbeck...

88
00:34:33.196 --> 00:34:36.029
...I have concluded that your treaty...

89
00:34:36.199 --> 00:34:41.034
...is not in the best interest of my people.

90
00:34:41.804 --> 00:34:45.433
-Sir. if I may--
-So sorry...

91
00:34:45.808 --> 00:34:47.571
...but you may not.

92
00:34:47.910 --> 00:34:51.243
This is an outrage!

93
00:35:57.847 --> 00:36:00.372
Tell me how he died.

94
00:36:08.124 --> 00:36:12.686
I will tell you how he lived.

95
00:36:21.938 --> 00:36:26.375
And so the days
of the Samurai had ended.

96
00:36:26.542 --> 00:36:32.071
Nations. like men. it is sometimes said.
have their own destiny.

97
00:36:33.149 --> 00:36:35.743
As for the American captain...

98
00:36:35.918 --> 00:36:38.250
...no one knows what became of him.

99
00:36:38.421 --> 00:36:41.857
Some say that he died of his wounds...

100
00:36:42.024 --> 00:36:45.983
...others. that he returned
to his own country.

101
00:36:46.162 --> 00:36:47.789
But I like to think...

102
00:36:47.964 --> 00:36:53.027
...he may have at last found
some small measure of peace...

103
00:36:53.202 --> 00:36:55.193
... that we all seek...

104
00:36:55.972 --> 00:36:59.135
...and few of us ever find.

105
00:47:24.066 --> 00:47:26.057
[ENGLlSH]

106
00:47:27.305 --> 00:48:27.184
